The paper discusses the use of software-defined networking and artificial intelligence in the development and deployment of smart city projects, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the importance of big data in smart city projects, which could be categorized under databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential security implications of implementing these technologies in smart city projects, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CY) or cryptography (cs.CR).
